# LED Blink with Potentiometer Control

## Objective
To control the blinking speed of an LED using a potentiometer while displaying real-time values on the Serial Monitor.

## Hardware Required
- Arduino UNO
- LED
- 220Ω Resistor
- 10kΩ Potentiometer
- Breadboard
- Jumper Wires
- USB Cable

## Circuit Description
The LED is connected to digital pin 13 through a current-limiting resistor. The potentiometer is connected between 5V and GND, with its middle pin connected to analog pin A0. The Arduino reads the analog value and adjusts the LED blinking speed accordingly.

## Software
- Arduino IDE
- Tinkercad

## Program Features
- LED blinking
- Serial Monitor output
- Adjustable blink speed
- Analog input using potentiometer

## Expected Output
- The LED blinks continuously.
- Rotating the potentiometer changes the blinking speed.
- The Serial Monitor displays the potentiometer value and calculated delay.

## Troubleshooting
- Verify all wiring connections.
- Ensure the resistor is connected correctly.
- Check that the potentiometer middle pin is connected to A0.
- Confirm the correct board and port are selected before uploading.

